<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="50">
Trichomycteridae is a monophyletic group composed of eight subfamilies, 41 genera and about of 173 nominal species (de Pinna &amp; Wosiacki, 2003), with many more to be described. Seven subfamilies are demonstrably monophyletic groups, but Trichomycterinae is the largest and clearly a polyphyletic group of Trichomycteridae (Wosiacki, 2002). Trichomycterinae is composed of five monotypic genera (
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F62CC6A5-AB30-43DE-8B00-8A4B4ECC8D5F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Eremophilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Eremophilus Humboldt 1805:35" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Eremophilus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:ECB425E2-93CB-442F-A98F-F534D03786D9" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Hatcheria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hatcheria Eigenmann 1909:250" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hatcheria</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:BBFF8CF7-9C52-4807-A2C6-CD0DE06C7EC9" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Bullockia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bullockia Arratia, Chang G, Menu-Marque &amp; Rojas M 1978:162" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Bullockia</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A676D0ED-F931-44EF-B95E-3251C0ECB9DC" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Silvinichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Silvinichthys Arratia 1998:356" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Silvinichthys</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3FCF33D0-E804-474F-ADFB-4BB4586D1EFE" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Rhizosomichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rhizosomichthys Miles 1943:369" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rhizosomichthys</taxonomicName>
), all defined by autapomorphies, and the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Trichomycterus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Trichomycterus</taxonomicName>
with about 100 species (de Pinna &amp; Wosiacki 2003) that form a non-monophyletic group (de Pinna, 1989). Costa &amp; Bockmann (1993) described the genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:FDAB162D-116C-4E81-B78B-D677333D2F85" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Ituglanis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Ituglanis Costa &amp; Bockmann 1993:44" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Ituglanis</taxonomicName>
composed of some species formerly included in the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Trichomycterus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Trichomycterus</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:65DF1862-8AEB-4CEE-A4E6-7A68596E525C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Scleronema" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Scleronema Eigenmann 1917:691" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Scleronema</taxonomicName>
was proposed as a sister group of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:FDAB162D-116C-4E81-B78B-D677333D2F85" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Ituglanis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Ituglanis Costa &amp; Bockmann 1993:44" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Ituglanis</taxonomicName>
plus a large intrafamilial clade (Glanapteryginae, Sarcoglanidinae, Tridentinae, Stegophilinae and Vandelliinae) (Costa &amp; Bockmann, 1993), although no subfamilial rank was proposed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="50">
Despite the large number of species already known for “ 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Trichomycterus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Trichomycterus</taxonomicName>
”, many species have been recently described (Barbosa &amp; Costa, 2003; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Fernández">Fernandez</normalizedToken>
&amp; Schaefer, 2003; Bockmann &amp; Sazima, 2004; Bockmann et al. 2004; Triques &amp; Vono, 2004; Wosiacki &amp; Garavello, 2004; and Wosiacki, 2004), and the real estimate of the diversity within the genus is far from complete. Species-level identification within 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Trichomycterus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Trichomycterus</taxonomicName>
is often precluded by the scarce information available on most nominal species. For these reasons, redescriptions of poorly known species are crucial (Arratia, 1998; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Fernández">Fernandez</normalizedToken>
, 2000) to achieve a better taxonomic and systematic knowledge of the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
